Making a new class

Add to `class`, with auto class_id

Note class_id.

Add to `class_level` for each level of the class

SELECT FROM `class_level` WHERE `class_id` = 6 INTO OUTFILE 'monk_class'

LOAD DATA INFILE  'monk_class' 
INTO TABLE `class_level`
(@var1, hd_advance, level, special_abilities, bonus_feat, spell_advancement, spells_per_day, spells_known, skill_array)
SET class_id  = 197


Add to `skill_list` (if existing class similar, use:

"SELECT * FROM 'skill_list' WHERE 'class_id' = x INTO OUTFILE 'new_list'"

then

"LOAD DATA INFILE 'new_skill' INTO TABLE `skill_list` (@var1, @var2, skill_id) SET `class_id` = newx, description = 'new class'"

then add new records for additional skills